        <h2>23. Moringaceae (Drumstick Family)</h2>
        <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Moringa (Drumstick tree).</p>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong> 
            The Moringaceae family is known for its nutrient-dense leaves and seeds, particularly Moringa, which is widely used for food, fodder, and medicinal purposes. These trees are highly drought-tolerant and thrive in arid conditions.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Roles:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Highly Nutritious Leaves, Seeds, & Pods:</strong> Used as a superfood and animal fodder.</li>
            <li><strong>Drought Tolerance:</strong> Thrives in arid and semi-arid regions.</li>
            <li><strong>Animal Fodder & Biomass:</strong> Provides high-protein feed and improves soil fertility.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

