        <h2>24. Betulaceae (Birch Family)</h2>
        <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Birch, hazelnut, alder.</p>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong> 
            The Betulaceae family includes trees and shrubs known for their fast growth and adaptability. Some members, such as alders, are nitrogen-fixing, while others, like hazelnuts, provide valuable edible nuts.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Roles:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Edible Nuts:</strong> Hazelnuts provide a valuable food source.</li>
            <li><strong>Nitrogen Fixation (Alder Species):</strong> Improves soil fertility and supports ecosystem health.</li>
            <li><strong>Timber & Firewood:</strong> Provides durable wood for construction and fuel.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

