        <p><strong>Description:</strong> 
            The Proteaceae family includes nutrient-efficient plants adapted to poor soils. Many species are valued for their edible nuts, striking flowers, and ability to thrive in low-fertility conditions.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Roles:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Edible Nuts:</strong> Macadamia nuts are a high-value crop.</li>
            <li><strong>Wildlife Attractor:</strong> Flowers support pollinators, particularly birds.</li>
            <li><strong>Adaptation to Nutrient-Poor Soils:</strong> Thrives in challenging environments.</li>
